    "title": "Delhi",
    "content": "Delhi is a city of immense historical and cultural significance, serving as the capital of numerous empires throughout history, including the Delhi Sultanate and the Mughal Empire. Its geography is dominated by the Yamuna River, which flows through the city, dividing it into East and West Delhi. The modern city is a complex blend of ancient monuments, bustling markets, and modern infrastructure, reflecting centuries of layered history. It functions as the political, administrative, and cultural hub of India, hosting major governmental institutions and numerous educational and cultural centers. The National Capital Region (NCR) surrounding Delhi is one of the most populous metropolitan areas globally.",
